file=Product/price/operational/skill/price-skill-routing.md · p—s:price — Skill Routing Map=Non-leader: law (the Evidence Gate — price runs it for monetization) + this routing decide WHICH skill WHEN.\n\n```\nnew price / no WTP evidence ─► pricing-research (WTP by segment; value-anchored; flagged methods)\n│ WTP structure\n▼\npackaging-tiers (value metric; good/better/best; feature→tier; fences)\n│ structure\n▼\npricing-experiment-discipline (loom's rigor + blast-radius rules; new/holdout only)\n│ won test\n▼\nprice-change-governance (impact; grandfather; board if locked commitment) ─► ship ─► metric reads revenue+churn\n```\n\nHandoffs out: loom (revenue experiments, registry) \· metric (revenue-per-user, churn instrumentation) \· board/precedent (locked-commitment changes, Fleet Charter Rail 3) \· echo/comms (change communication) \· felix/Finance/future (margin/unit-economics boundary) \· spec (feature-to-tier seam) \· mia/Engineering (pricing-page build) \· anneal (a mispriced-and-missed outcome → skill lesson).\nPrecedence: research proposes, revenue experiments confirm; existing customers never silently repriced; locked commitments → board; every change is a logged proposal.\n